Facts Mark Kelly (D) is the incumbent, he unseated Martha McSally (R) in a special election in 2022 Martha McSally was appointed to the position in 2018 and had a previously loss for the other Arizona seat 2018 was the last governor election in Arizona, Doug Ducey ® won with 56% of the vote Mark Kelly’s margin has shrunk since May going from +10 to +2 (for Brnovich only) Ducey net unfavorables increase when federal investigation and covid response to brought up The Republican candidate has not yet been selected, prelim polling shows slight margin for Mark Kelly Currently race is considered a toss up Mark Kelly has fundraising of ~$18M, this inline with prior D candidates Arizona has typically had a Republican lean, however recent senate election have been won by D’s and Biden flipped Arizona Pima & Maricopa county generally determine the election due to their population size, in 2018 D’s won them with 56.65% and 50.96% of the vote respectively Early polling in 2020 and 2018 was predictive (538 polling), early polling has limited sample size but polling closer to the election date tends to become noisier Bidens approval ratings is similar to Trumps at the same time in their term
